---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="I Beat Economics">
  <div style="padding: 2rem 0 1rem;">
    <h1>I Beat<br /><span style="color: var(--blue);">Economics</span></h1>
    <p style="margin-top: 0.75rem; font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--text-muted); max-width: 520px; line-height: 1.7;">
      Class notes, key terms, worked examples and exercises — topic by topic.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">Units</h2>
    <div class="topic-grid">
      <a href="/ibecon/unit1/" class="topic-card">
        <div class="card-num">Unit 1</div>
        <div class="card-title">Introduction to Economics</div>
        <div class="card-desc">
          What economics is, the economic problem, opportunity cost, PPC, circular flow, and how economists think.
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="/ibecon/unit2/" class="topic-card">
        <div class="card-num">Unit 2</div>
        <div class="card-title">Microeconomics</div>
        <div class="card-desc">
          Demand, supply, equilibrium, elasticities, government intervention, externalities, market failures, and market power (HL).
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="/ibecon/unit3/" class="topic-card">
        <div class="card-num">Unit 3</div>
        <div class="card-title">Macroeconomics</div>
        <div class="card-desc">
          Measuring output, AD/AS, growth, unemployment, inflation, inequality, monetary policy, fiscal policy, and supply-side policies.
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="/ibecon/unit4/" class="topic-card coming-soon">
        <div class="card-num">Unit 4</div>
        <div class="card-title">The Global Economy</div>
        <div class="card-desc">
          International trade, protection, exchange rates, balance of payments, development, and sustainability.
        </div>
        <span class="card-coming">To come</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
